        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 1:53PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 153 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Merriam Woods, or near Forsyth, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elkhead, Chestnutridge, Emerald Beach, Silver Dollar City, Spokane,
Rockaway Beach, Kirbyville, Chain-O-Lakes, Chadwick, Blue Eye, Nixa,
Sparta, Table Rock, Selmore, Keltner, Lampe, Kimberling City,
Taneyville, Branson, and Ozark Beach.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
